snippet.textDisplay:
Are you sure Bungie "accidentally" enabled crossplay in Destiny 2?
Perhaps they thought something like
"Okay, so we implemented a lot of the crossplay features now, but we only had some really small tests. Will it still hold up when we throw a shit load of gamers at it? It would be good to know that now, so we avoid working into the completely wrong direction for months."
"Why don't we just do a public alpha test?"
"Hell NO! The game is already out but this feature is still in an early development phase and most gamers just don't understand that, will expect too much, and will get angry at us when it doesn't work as expected."
"Okay, perhaps they understand it when we 'accidentally' release it, wich would make it seem legit to take it down shortly after that. They don't just won't get mad, they will think we are the nice guys because we don't take it down immediately."

Just a note from myself. I think this would be absolutely legit. A lot of gamers are stupid, don't understand what it means to develop a game, and get angry for no reason.
